1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:05,800
I want a divorce.

4
00:00:06,633 --> 00:00:07,933
Divorce?

5
00:00:09,133 --> 00:00:11,033
I can't live with you anymore.

6
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,100
So let's separate.

7
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:16,100
Mom, Dad.

8
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:19,100
No, don't worry, Bit Na.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,333
Dad disappointed Mom a little,

10
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:24,600
so she's really angry right now.

11
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,400
But Mom and Dad are never separating.
Never.

12
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,500
Really, Mom?

13
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,700
You're not leaving Dad, right?

14
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:38,200
Of course not.
When you fight with your friend,

15
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,500
you say you'll never play with them again,
but then you play together again, right?

16
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,300
It's like that for Mom and Dad too.

17
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,300
Right, honey?

18
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,533
I'll definitely make her feel better.

19
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:56,600
So Bit Na, don't worry about anything...

20
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,500
and just stay in your room, okay?

21
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:00,200
Promise.

22
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,100
Okay, promise. Pinky promise.

23
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,100
(Episode 21)

24
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:17,400
I'm sorry. I know I disappointed you,

25
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:20,600
but it's something I absolutely cannot do.

26
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,600
Eun Ae sent the money.

27
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,533
Call them right now
and say we'll wire the donation, please.

28
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:30,233
Eun Ae sent the money?

29
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:33,300
Yes, 200,000 dollars
just came into my account.

30
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:35,233
Don't tell me you asked Eun Ae
for money too.

31
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,600
Seriously, why is everyone...

32
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:42,400
Return it to Eun Ae right now!

33
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,133
Even if it means divorcing me,

34
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,733
you'd still refuse to become a professor
by paying the donation?

35
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,533
Honey, no matter what job I do,

36
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,700
I'll be the provider, okay?

37
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:52,800
Even with what I earn now,

38
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,700
our family won't starve.

39
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:57,833
If it really didn't matter
what kind of work you did,

40
00:01:57,833 --> 00:01:59,800
would I have been living like this?

41
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,600
Do you really not know
why I endured all this until now?

42
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:04,600
You don't know what I wanted?

43
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:08,733
So you put up with me
because I'd become a professor?

44
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,333
That's not it!

45
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:20,933
Getting your PhD and drifting...

46
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:22,400
from one temporary teaching job
to another...

47
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:25,000
Wasn't it all for becoming a professor?

48
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,833
That's your dream too.

49
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,100
Of course it is my dream.

50
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,633
But even so,

51
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:34,133
I can't make the wrong choice.

52
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:37,033
So your conscience and values...

53
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,333
matter more than our family?

54
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,500
Really?

55
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,200
Choose.

56
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,300
Either pay the donation
and become a professor,

57
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,733
or divorce me for real.

58
00:02:49,733 --> 00:02:51,333
Ji Seon!

59
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:00,133
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

60
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,500
Why won't she answer the phone?

61
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,600
Please pick up.

62
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,400
Why the underground parking lot
instead of the main gate?

63
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:19,533
Do you want
the whole neighborhood talking?

64
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,233
(Mom)

65
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,900
Why aren't you answering?

66
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:30,633
Someone's been calling nonstop.

67
00:03:32,433 --> 00:03:33,800
Is it your boyfriend?

68
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:37,300
I doubt you already have one.

69
00:03:37,933 --> 00:03:38,900
What did you say?

70
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:41,400
I mean, in general, you are...

71
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,733
As someone who is very strict about time,

72
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:45,600
may I leave work now?

73
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,833
It's almost time to clock out.

74
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,500
Well, it's not as if you can't.

75
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,533
Then I'll get going.

76
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,900
I'm working late.

77
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,800
What?

78
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,900
I'm not saying you have to work late too.

79
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:00,433
I want to buy you dinner
as thanks for the ride.

80
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,833
No. In general,

81
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:06,000
I tend to eat
with people I'm comfortable with. Goodbye.

82
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,000
What?
Is she saying I make her uncomfortable?

83
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:19,700
Is it the clothes?

84
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,333
What have you been making over there
this whole time?

85
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,333
It's almost done.

86
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:28,700
What is this?

87
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,400
Cheese bindaetteok. Try it.

88
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:35,300
What is this stretchy string-like thing?

89
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:44,133
What did you do to our bindaetteok?

90
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:47,033
Our bindaetteok is more for adult tastes,
right?

91
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:49,800
So I'm developing a new menu...

92
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,733
that everyone can enjoy.
What do you think?

93
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,900
Quiet.

94
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,033
What's the trademark of our place?

95
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:58,500
Original bindaetteok, right?

96
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,800
And you're doing this stupid thing?

97
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,933
What do you mean, stupid?

98
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:07,100
Retro is the trend these days.

99
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,500
All it needs is just one drop...

100
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,833
of something Millennials and Gen Z like...

101
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:11,833
Enough.

102
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:14,100
Hey.

103
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:17,300
Give me back that bankbook I gave you.

104
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:21,200
What? Don't they say if you take back
what you gave, you'll grow horns?

105
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,700
I'm not asking for all of it.

106
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:28,300
If Eun Hyeong doesn't get 200,000 dollars
right away, he'll be unemployed.

107
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:30,500
I need to add whatever I can.

108
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:33,300
What? Eun Hyeong will be unemployed?

109
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:37,700
I'm home.

110
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:42,100
Why weren't you answering your phone?

111
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:44,300
Why? Did something happen?

112
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:46,200
Your brother turned down the foundation.

113
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,233
I'm thinking of taking that money
right now...

114
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:50,700
and going to beg
the foundation people somehow,

115
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,400
so hurry up and give me your money.

116
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,400
Hey, Eun Ae. Cho Eun Ae...

117
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:04,700
Open the door!

118
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:06,733
Eun Ae.

119
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,533
Eun Ae, open the door!

120
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,600
Eun Ae!

121
00:06:12,433 --> 00:06:14,733
Hey! Seriously...

122
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:19,200
What are you doing? Open the door!

123
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,900
Hey, Eun Ae, open the door!

124
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,200
Cho Eun Ae!

125
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,400
My goodness, what should I do?

126
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,233
What are you doing?

127
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:31,700
Honey, what do we do?
Eun Hyeong turned down the professorship.

128
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,833
Please talk to Eun Ae. Tell her
we'll pay her back with the severance pay.

129
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,500
Ask her to save her brother.

130
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,000
Honey, please calm down.

131
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,800
Do I look like I can calm down right now?

132
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:44,300
If Eun Ae just gives the money,
I can go myself and beg again...

133
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,200
Eun Hyeong already told them
he won't do it.

134
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:48,133
What exactly are you going to beg for?

135
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,700
Are you really okay
with Eun Hyeong becoming unemployed?

136
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:53,000
Please, honey!

137
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:56,000
Let's go downstairs, okay?
Come downstairs and talk to me.

138
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,733
Okay? Hurry.

139
00:06:58,133 --> 00:07:00,433
How can she be so cold-hearted?

140
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:01,433
Come down, honey!

141
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,700
(Kangsu Construction)

142
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,433
You're still working?

143
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:03,433
Yes.

144
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:06,133
But what's with those childish slippers?

145
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:08,000
It's nothing.

146
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:12,900
Wait, those slippers
look similar to Ms. Cho Eun Ae's.

147
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,900
What? Are you two matching?

148
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,000
What are you talking about?

149
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,433
What do you think, Manager Seo?

150
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,100
I'll pass on silly jokes.

151
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:25,100
What do you mean, silly? It's obvious...

152
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,100
Got you.

153
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,433
You even have Ms. Cho's photo open
on your monitor.

154
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,100
That's not what this is.

155
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:35,600
You insisted on taking responsibility
and brought her in as an intern,

156
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:37,733
and the two of you went for a third round
after the team dinner.

157
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,933
Not two, we were three.

158
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,800
Anyway, with that photo on your monitor,

159
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,700
this is basically saying you're a couple,
isn't it?

160
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:49,233
I'll be leaving first.

161
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:51,700
Manager Seo, wait.

162
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,000
Manager Seo.

163
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,800
What's wrong? Are you mad?

164
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,600
No, I don't think I can work here today.

165
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,600
I'll finish it at home.

166
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:13,033
Why? Because I was pairing
Gyeol and Cho Eun Ae together?

167
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,200
I'll get going now.

168
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,433
Seo Seung Ri, you feel it too, don't you?

169
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,400
That something's going on
between Gyeol and Cho Eun Ae.

170
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,733
Ko Gyeol and Cho Eun Ae.

171
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,500
I like the sound of that.

172
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,533
What? An insult?

173
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,500
Humiliation?

174
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:42,933
So you're saying you can't work together?

175
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,300
- No, I can't!
- No, I can't!

176
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,133
To me, having this perverted psycho...

177
00:09:47,133 --> 00:09:49,700
draw my novel is an insult in itself.

178
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,400
An insult?

179
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:54,400
Seriously, this woman...

180
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,900
What? You want to fight?

181
00:09:58,600 --> 00:09:59,900
What kind of ridiculous situation is this?

182
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,300
Ms. Cho, if this novel becomes
a successful webtoon,

183
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,533
it could turn into a drama later.

184
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:09,800
This is your golden chance
to become a star writer.

185
00:10:10,033 --> 00:10:12,633
Then assign me a different webtoon artist.

186
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,933
As long as it's not him, I'm all in.

187
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,900
Who are you to talk?

188
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:21,233
As long as it's not this thug of a writer,
anyone's fine.

189
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,733
Mr. Seo Seung Wu, think carefully, okay?

190
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,200
You don't even have a winning title...

191
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,200
or serialization experience to show.

192
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,100
What are you saying right now?

193
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,100
Wait a second.

194
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:34,933
Excuse me,
the more I listen, the worse I feel.

195
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:38,500
Yes, I may be a rookie with no awards...

196
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,700
and no serialization history,

197
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,400
but then what about her?

198
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,900
Is she some great writer or something?

199
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:48,100
You really don't know?
Let me tell you who she is...

200
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:51,533
Sir, even hearing this perverted psycho...

201
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:54,500
mention my work is humiliating enough,

202
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:56,800
so no comment.

203
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:59,000
What? Humiliating?

204
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,133
Die!

205
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:12,700
My stomach.

206
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:16,100
That perverted psycho...

207
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:19,400
stressed me out so much
I feel like I'm getting stomach cramps.

208
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,433
Out of all the webtoon artists
in the world,

209
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:24,133
why did it have to be him?

210
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:26,933
Forget it.

211
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:32,300
At times like this,
talking to Napkin Genius is the best cure.

212
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,900
Die!

213
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,400
Die!

214
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,400
Die!

215
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,500
It's Oh My Oz.

216
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:46,000
How did your meeting go today,
Napkin Genius?

217
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,400
Don't even ask, Oh My Oz.

218
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:52,133
Today is a day
I'd rather not even remember.

219
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:54,833
Why?

220
00:11:55,433 --> 00:11:58,900
I went to a meeting too
and stepped on a landmine.

221
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:02,500
I stepped on a landmine, a nuclear bomb,
and even dog poop.

222
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,400
Oh My Oz, the more I think about it,

223
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:12,833
I think we're destined.

224
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,800
Destined?

225
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,700
Yes. Otherwise, how could we keep...

226
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:19,833
sharing the exact same experiences
every time?

227
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,800
Let's meet right now.

228
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:24,900
Right now.

229
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:29,700
Should we?

230
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:32,300
But meeting right now is a little hard.

231
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,000
How about this weekend?

232
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:39,700
Deal.
You pick the time and place, Oh My Oz.

233
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:44,000
But how will we recognize each other?

234
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,800
Don't worry.

235
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,800
After all the soul-level connection
we've had,

236
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:51,000
I feel like I'll recognize you right away.

237
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:54,200
I'll run straight to you, Oh My Oz.

238
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:05,900
Even though the contract fell through,
your appetite seems perfectly fine.

239
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:08,733
This and that are different.

240
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:11,500
You hated the collaboration partner
that much?

241
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,200
She was a total nuclear bomb,
a landmine, and...

242
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:18,800
She was just a complete no.

243
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,100
Even if you don't like the other person,

244
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:24,433
can you really throw away
such a good opportunity like that?

245
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,000
Since the producer recognized my genius,

246
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,400
I'm sure he'll match me
with another writer soon enough.

247
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,433
By the way,

248
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,100
what work of yours did that producer see
to think you had potential?

249
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,033
Don't tell me...

250
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,833
"Secretary by Nature?"

251
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:44,500
What? That's not my only work.

252
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,400
Hello, Chairman. Yes.

253
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,500
As expected, it suits him.

254
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,600
Did you really delete that work?

255
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:03,400
I told you, I did.

256
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:07,400
If your dad ever sees it, you're dead.

257
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,133
How is it?
As Grandma's Bindaetteok's new menu.

258
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:20,033
For a first try, it's not bad.

259
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:23,800
What's with that lethargic reaction?

260
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:26,700
It's because of Eun Hyeong, right?

261
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,533
I heard from Grandma...

262
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,633
that you and your mom fought
over Eun Hyeong's donation.

263
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:36,700
Sorry for bringing that up.

264
00:14:37,813 --> 00:14:39,074
Right.

265
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,900
How's the love triangle
in your team going?

266
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,500
What? What love triangle?

267
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,733
You dummy, how do I explain this simply?

268
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:51,100
Look, this red one is the CPO.

269
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:53,633
The gray one is the Team Manager.

270
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:57,600
The orange one is the Senior Manager,
and you're this yellow one.

271
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:00,900
The CPO likes the Senior Manager,

272
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:04,700
and the Senior Manager
likes the Team Manager,

273
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:08,900
but by some twist of fate,
the Team Manager's arrow...

274
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,333
Arrow what?

275
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:13,200
It looks like it might go to you.
Maybe, maybe not.

276
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,600
I'm leaving.

277
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:18,400
(Kangsu Construction)

278
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:21,200
Mr. Kim, Ms. Cho,
shall we have our meeting?

279
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:26,900
Team Manager,
is our team finally having a meeting?

280
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,900
Yes.
Gather in the meeting room in ten minutes.

281
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:32,333
Okay. Yes!

282
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:33,933
Why the laptop?

283
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,500
We need to open the server
for the meeting.

284
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,400
No need. Just bring your notebook.

285
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:47,433
By the way, Ms. Cho,

286
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,533
where on earth did you get those slippers?

287
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:54,933
They sell these at my neighborhood market.
Want me to get you a pair?

288
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,033
Then can you get me cat slippers?

289
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,900
Let's observe some TPO.
This is a company, not a kindergarten.

290
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,400
Okay.

291
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,800
This is our team's first meeting today,

292
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,000
so let's talk freely.

293
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:12,800
I've been gathering excellent examples...

294
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,200
of retirement communities
from around the world.

295
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:17,800
You've been working hard on your own.
What about you, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

296
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:20,933
Me? I just...

297
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,400
What about your thoughts, Team Manager?

298
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,900
You must've had some plan in mind...

299
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,533
with all those fieldwork trips, right?

300
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,900
I've only drawn one line on a blank page.

301
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:33,100
Nature and people will come in,

302
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,600
and buildings will be placed last.

303
00:16:36,733 --> 00:16:38,200
I'm not really sure what that means...

304
00:16:39,033 --> 00:16:42,000
In other words, the most important thing
in our retirement community...

305
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,100
The people.
The elderly who will live there.

306
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,600
We need to build a home for them.
That's the point, right?

307
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,000
Yes, exactly.

308
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,433
Buildings exist for people.

309
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:55,800
In short,
a nature-friendly home for the elderly.

310
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,433
Bingo.
And the next thing to think about is,

311
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:01,300
"What do they need most?"

312
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,200
Wouldn't it be
a convenient living environment?

313
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Friends.

314
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:07,633
I agree.

315
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:10,733
People moving into retirement communities
are older, of course,

316
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:12,633
but many of them
also have mobility issues...

317
00:17:12,633 --> 00:17:14,100
or are alone.

318
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:15,700
I agree.

319
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,000
For people like that,
loneliness is the biggest enemy.

320
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,400
So what they need most is friends.

321
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:21,700
Exactly.

322
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:29,700
So Gyeol finally started having meetings?

323
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,200
Yes.

324
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,400
What do you think Gyeol's concept is
for the retirement community?

325
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:36,300
How would I know that?

326
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:39,000
Know your enemy and know yourself,
and you won't be in danger.

327
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,700
Isn't it "win every battle?"

328
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,700
Sun Tzu said, "Know your enemy...

329
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:47,000
and know yourself,

330
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,100
and you won't be endangered
in a hundred battles."

331
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:51,433
Don't tell me you want me
to spy on Gyeol's team...

332
00:17:51,433 --> 00:17:53,500
and steal information?

333
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:56,233
I have absolutely no intention...

334
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:58,700
of competing with Gyeol
using such cheap tricks.

335
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,200
Cheap trick or deep trick,

336
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:03,400
you use whatever you can, you idiot.

337
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:06,500
If you're done, I'll be going.

338
00:18:08,533 --> 00:18:09,900
Seriously, that brat...

339
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:11,833
Wait a second.

340
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:16,300
Mr. Ju, come in for a moment.

341
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:26,200
Did you call for me, sir?

342
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:30,200
Why are you acting like this?
It feels weird.

343
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,933
Please sit down.

344
00:18:39,133 --> 00:18:40,233
Have you thought about it?

345
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,900
About stepping back from the front line...

346
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,000
and supporting Father from home.

347
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:48,900
No matter what anyone says,
I'm your assistant.

348
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,500
Who said you weren't?

349
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:53,333
And since I'm your boss,

350
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,300
you should do as I say.

351
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:59,300
I'm thinking of giving your seat...

352
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,600
to Seong Jun.

353
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:05,600
You know how capable Seong Jun is, right?

354
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,333
I guess you don't know
my abilities very well.

355
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:11,033
When it comes to brains,
mine is quite impressive too.

356
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:15,300
March 10, 1980.
Kangsu Construction was established.

357
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:18,000
In 2001, the first in-house brand,

358
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,033
Kangsu Apartments, was completed.

359
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:20,833
May 18 of the same year,

360
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:22,700
Kangsu Construction won
Outstanding Small and Medium Enterprise.

361
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,800
- In August of 2005...
- Enough.

362
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,100
Stop right there.

363
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:27,700
No...

364
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,500
I'm not kicking you out completely.

365
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,400
You can still keep protecting
my body and mind like now,

366
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,833
but the assistant office is already full.

367
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,100
You need to leave so I can...

368
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:40,833
No, there needs to be an opening.

369
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,833
Then promise me one thing.

370
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:46,800
Even if your friend Seong Jun comes,

371
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:49,833
my title stays the same.

372
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,033
Of course.

373
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,833
And I will keep my four major insurances.

374
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,000
Not just four,
I'll give you eight insurances.

375
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,300
Life insurance, whole life insurance,
whatever.

376
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:00,700
And...

377
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Starting today, I'll drive myself,

378
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:05,800
so you can just comfortably go home now,
okay?

379
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,200
Then at home...

380
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:11,700
I'm dropping the formal speech, okay?

381
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,233
Dropping...

382
00:20:14,233 --> 00:20:15,633
Sure, speak casually.

383
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,500
Yes, go ahead. Thanks.

384
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,500
Let me think. So I'm done with Yong Man.

385
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,733
Now, I just need to persuade Seong Jun.

386
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,500
Perfect, I'm so happy.

387
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:35,000
Take good care of my boss.

388
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,200
What?

389
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,500
He acts tough on the outside
for no reason,

390
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:45,333
but deep down, he's actually soft.

391
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:47,833
I'm not sure what you mean.

392
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:51,700
You'll find out soon enough.

393
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:01,833
What's with him?

394
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,033
Hey, Dae Chi.

395
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,300
Tonight?

396
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,500
Unless it's something special,
can we do it another time?

397
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:17,100
There's been a lot going on
at home lately,

398
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:18,800
so I need to get home early.

399
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:21,633
Yeah, okay. Bye.

400
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:29,200
So you decided to go along
with what CEO Ko wants?

401
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,400
Well, he wants it so badly.

402
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:36,000
I'll see how well he does without me.

403
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,200
You made the right choice.

404
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:42,433
Only when you're gone
will he realize how much he needs you.

405
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:45,133
Checkmate.

406
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:48,300
You struck my weak point.

407
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:50,600
It's time for your medicine.

408
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:53,733
Thank you, Yeong Hwa.

409
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:04,900
You two always look so good together.

410
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,033
I'm home.

411
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,533
Welcome back.

412
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,933
I thought you went to exercise.

413
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:15,633
From the look of it, you went shopping
at the department store again.

414
00:22:15,633 --> 00:22:17,900
These are for Father and Mother.

415
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,533
For us?

416
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:21,733
Yes, open them.

417
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,000
What?

418
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,500
These are for us?

419
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,000
Of course.

420
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:34,600
You two even took vow renewal photos,

421
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:36,200
and tomorrow is your honeymoon.

422
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:39,400
Wear matching outfits and enjoy feeling
like newlyweds to the fullest.

423
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:42,400
That's a great idea.

424
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:46,200
I really love this.

425
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:50,933
What? Those are young people's clothes.

426
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:53,633
Since when do clothes have an age limit?

427
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,200
I really like this.

428
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:59,400
Looks like you finally got a hole-in-one.

429
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:02,000
I get hole-in-ones often, you know.

430
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:06,233
Yes, I just brought her home.

431
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:11,633
Today is my last lecture,

432
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,100
so the department head and everyone
are having a farewell dinner together.

433
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,500
Your last lecture?

434
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,200
I won't be too late. I'll hang up.

435
00:23:31,633 --> 00:23:34,100
What's wrong?
You haven't said a word since earlier.

436
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:36,600
Did you fight with a friend?

437
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,500
Then, are you sick?

438
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:44,100
Grandma, my mom and dad...

439
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:46,233
might get divorced.

440
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:48,833
What?

441
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:53,033
Did the meeting go well?

442
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:54,900
Yes.

443
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:59,500
But why do you look like that, Mr. Kim?

444
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,833
It's just...

445
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,600
I can't really make sense of it,

446
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:06,200
but Team Manager and Ms. Cho
work together so well...

447
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:08,000
that I'm kind of stunned.

448
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,433
Do they really have something going on?

449
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:19,100
Now share the server with me.
That's how we'll integrate Joy.

450
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:23,633
You accepted the intern offer
for another reason, didn't you?

451
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,700
Wait a second.

452
00:24:31,233 --> 00:24:33,133
(Excluded, separate specification)

453
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,733
Another reason? What do you mean by that?

454
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,300
You should know better than anyone.

455
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,400
Anyway, postpone that goal for six months.

456
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:45,200
I have no idea what you're talking about.

457
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:48,400
I know Joy was made for the elderly.

458
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,300
And now I'm going to build one too,

459
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:52,733
a comfortable retirement community...

460
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:53,900
where old age can be happy and not lonely.

461
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,733
Don't you want to use Joy there properly?

462
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:02,633
You don't want Joy being used
for something completely different, right?

463
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:06,400
Of course not.
I want to handle my precious Joy...

464
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:07,800
Then wait six months.

465
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:11,033
Let's do this properly together
for six months.

466
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,033
A real home for the elderly.

467
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:20,133
I'm home.

468
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,200
What's wrong, Mom?

469
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,500
Are you happy now?

470
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:31,833
Eun Hyeong lost his professorship
and might even end up divorced.

471
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,700
What? What do you mean?

472
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,033
If only you had given the money on time,

473
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:37,033
he wouldn't have lost that position,

474
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:39,933
and Ji Seon would have no reason
to ask for a divorce.

475
00:25:40,933 --> 00:25:42,000
Divorce?

476
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:46,100
Are you saying that, because of me,

477
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,000
Eun Hyeong lost his professorship
and might get divorced?

478
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,033
What else do you think I'm saying?

479
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:54,700
Mom, how can you do this to me?

480
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:57,100
No, how can you?

481
00:25:57,300 --> 00:25:58,800
Are you even part of this family
if you act like this?

482
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:02,900
I guess you really didn't want me
to make it back home back then.

483
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,033
Found it.

484
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,400
Eun Ae!

485
00:26:25,733 --> 00:26:27,300
- Eun Ae!
- Eun Ae!

486
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:28,300
Eun Ae!

487
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,000
You little brat.

488
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,400
Where did you go?

489
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:38,700
If you were going somewhere,
you should've told me first!

490
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,533
Do you know how hard I looked for you?

491
00:26:41,533 --> 00:26:42,533
Mom.

492
00:26:42,533 --> 00:26:44,533
Now that we found her, that's enough.
Don't be like that, honey.

493
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:47,400
Let me take a look at you.

494
00:26:49,100 --> 00:26:52,200
You fell down. That must've hurt a lot.

495
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:57,533
Look at you. What is this mess?

496
00:26:57,900 --> 00:27:00,533
Did you get so caught up playing
you forgot it was getting dark?

497
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:04,333
And why did you pick this thing up
and bring it home?

498
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,700
Why are you crying? Stop it.

499
00:27:09,333 --> 00:27:12,200
Mom, I thought...

500
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,300
I thought you had abandoned me.

501
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:18,833
I was so scared.

502
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,200
Stop it.

503
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,233
Speak properly instead of stuttering!

504
00:27:23,233 --> 00:27:24,600
Mom.

505
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:31,133
You little troublemaker,
making me worry like this.

506
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,000
What?

507
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:36,100
I'm talking about that five-year-old girl
who you abandoned...

508
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:38,400
and don't even remember,
who might as well not exist.

509
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:41,700
Were you that disappointed
when she found her way home after all?

510
00:27:44,500 --> 00:27:45,833
You should've abandoned me again.

511
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:48,500
You should've made sure
I could never find my way home again!

512
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:52,233
What? Honey!

513
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:10,733
(Our Happy Days)

514
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,500
Sometimes you're so overly cheerful
it's hopeless,

515
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,900
and other times, like today,

516
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:17,233
you look like you're carrying
the weight of the whole world alone.

517
00:28:17,233 --> 00:28:19,100
Which one is the real Cho Eun Ae?

518
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:20,500
Oh My Oz?

519
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,033
Nice to meet you. I'm the Napkin...

520
00:28:22,033 --> 00:28:24,400
What? You're Napkin Genius?

521
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:26,000
What have I done?

522
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:27,800
What have I done to Eun Ae?

523
00:28:28,300 --> 00:28:29,433
Honey, call Eun Ae.

524
00:28:29,433 --> 00:28:30,500
Find out where she is.

525
00:28:30,933 --> 00:28:32,633
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
